<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-04-08T22:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-04-08T22:36:00-05:00" n="1300" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1300">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/3534.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-04-08T21:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 8, 1912—9 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>As the Mexican National Railway refused to grant any of the demands of
                            the American employees, these, amounting to from 700 to <pb facs="1035" n="919" xml:id="pg_919"/> 800, will strike on the 15th and leave
                            their posts. I have used all my influence with the Government, the
                            railways, and the men to prevent the crisis and am deeply disappointed
                            that no good result has followed.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>